INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to stem cell research.
EventItemMatterName: Stem Cell Research

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to the expenditure of payments in lieu of taxes and requiring a monthly report on the collection and use of all such payments to the City of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Expenditure of payments in lieu of taxes and requiring a monthly report on the collection and use of all such payments to NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution mourning the death and celebrating the life of Peter Zvi Malkin, the man who captured Adolph Eichmann.
EventItemMatterName: Mourning the death and celebrating the life of Peter Zvi Malkin.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution commemorating the second anniversary of the beginning of the war in Iraq on March 19, 2005, and calling on President George W. Bush to immediately withdraw all American troops from Iraq and further urging the United States Congress to reject the President’s request for additional funds for the war while at the same time making budget cuts to vital domestic programs.
EventItemMatterName: Commemorating the second anniversary of the beginning of the war in Iraq on March 19, 2005.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to support Congressman Charles Rangel’s proposed legislation, H.R. 677, which would grant permanent resident status to Amadou Diallo’s family members: Kadiatou Diallo, Laouratou Diallo, Ibrahima Diallo, Abdoul Diallo, Mamadou Bobo Diallo, Mamadou Pathe Diallo, Fatoumata Traore Diallo, Sankarela Diallo and Marliatou Bah.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to support Congressman Charles Rangel’s proposed legislation, H.R. 677, which would grant permanent resident status to Amadou Diallo’s family members.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the United States Congress to pass the Count Every Vote Act of 2005, introduced in the Senate by Senator Hillary Rodham Clinton and in the House by Representative Stephanie Tubbs Jones, a comprehensive package of pro-democracy, pro-voter legislation that contains the Civic Participation Act of 2005, a measure to restore voting rights in Federal elections to ex-offenders who have completed their sentences.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to pass the Count Every Vote Act of 2005.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to an annual Fire Department terrorism response drill.
EventItemMatterName: Annual Fire Department terrorism response drill.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to hazardous materials training for the emergency medical service.
EventItemMatterName: Hazardous materials training for the emergency medical service.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the re-establishment of a Fire Cadet program.
EventItemMatterName: Re-establishment of a Fire Cadet program.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to reforming the ranking procedure for the open competitive firefighter exam.
EventItemMatterName: Reforming the ranking procedure for the open competitive firefighter exam.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to providing separate women’s bathrooms and showers in all New York City firehouses.
EventItemMatterName: Providing separate women’s bathrooms and showers in all NYC firehouses.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to joint training by the hazardous materials teams of the New York City Fire Department and the New York City Police Department.
EventItemMatterName: Joint training by the hazardous materials teams of the NYC Fire Department and the NYC Police Department.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Congress of the United States to adopt legislation protecting the right to earn overtime pay and reversing the affects of detrimental new federal regulations that significantly weaken overtime protections.
EventItemMatterName: Protecting the right to earn overtime pay.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to extending funeral benefits to New York City auxiliary police officers.
EventItemMatterName: Extending funeral benefits to New York City auxiliary police officers.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Youth Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to tighten advertising restrictions in the federal Cigarette Labeling and Advertising Act and to allow localities to legislate in this area, in order to reduce the exposure of youth to tobacco advertising.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to tighten advertising restrictions in the federal Cigarette Labeling and Advertising Act.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Economic Development
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the appropriate committee of the Council of the City of New York to hold a hearing on the Mayor’s 2005 State of the City Address that announced the establishment of a “Commission on Construction Opportunity” and the “Building Jobs Through Building New York” initiative and on proposals from other parties that describe approaches to redress the historic and systemic denial of opportunities for minorities and women to receive their fair share of private and government contracts and employment in New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Hold a hearing on the Mayor’s 2005 State of the City Address.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the City of New York to allocate the Department of Parks and Recreation’s annual capital budget more equitably to all five boroughs, in that the Fiscal Year 2005 capital budget allocations only allotted 42.2% of the budget to the Bronx, Brooklyn, Queens and Staten Island, while 57.8% is allotted to Manhattan.
EventItemMatterName: Allocate the Department of Parks and Recreation’s annual capital budget more equitably to all five boroughs.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Mental Health, Mental Retardation, Alcoholism, Drug Abuse and Disability Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution opposing Governor Pataki’s decision to move the Jamaica office of the New York State Office of Temporary and Disability Assistance, Division of Disability Determinations, and up to 200 vital jobs, from its current location in downtown Jamaica, Queens.
EventItemMatterName: Opposing Governor Pataki’s decision to move the Jamaica office of the New York State Office of Temporary and Disability Assistance.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Senate to reject passage of S. 131, the Clear Skies Act of 2005, which undermines both the substance and spirit of the Clean Air Act, one of the nation’s landmark environmental laws.
EventItemMatterName: Senate to reject passage of S. 131, the Clear Skies Act of 2005.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to establishing a commission to study the feasibility of creating public/private partnerships to develop and operate job centers for immigrant day laborers.
EventItemMatterName: Establishing a commission to study the feasibility of creating public/private partnerships to develop and operate job centers for immigrant day laborers.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Mental Health, Mental Retardation, Alcoholism, Drug Abuse and Disability Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to maximizing the number of eligible New Yorkers enrolled in the federal food stamp program by developing an on-line application system.
EventItemMatterName: Maximizing the number of eligible New Yorkers enrolled in the federal food stamp program.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to maximizing the number of eligible New Yorkers enrolled in the federal food stamp program by distributing applications to emergency feeding programs throughout New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Maximizing the number of eligible New Yorkers enrolled in the federal food stamp program.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Mental Health, Mental Retardation, Alcoholism, Drug Abuse and Disability Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Governor of the State of New York to consider enacting legislation declaring psuedoephedrine, an essential ingredient in the making of methamphetamine, a controlled substance in order to restrict the of sale of over-the-counter cold medicine containing this ingredient, and further calling on the federal government to support the “Combat Meth Act of 2005.”
EventItemMatterName: Enact legislation declaring psuedoephedrine, an essential ingredient in the making of methamphetamine, a controlled substance.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to making the issuance of Metrocards to every first responder a requirement in order to adequately protect the public.
EventItemMatterName: Making the issuance of Metrocards to every first responder a requirement in order to adequately protect the public.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Small Business
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon President George W. Bush and the United States Congress to maintain funding in the proposed 2006 fiscal year federal budget for the Microloan program administered by the United States Small Business Administration.
EventItemMatterName: Maintain funding in the proposed FY'06 federal budget for the Microloan program administered by the US Small Business Administration.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the regulation of illegal alterations and conversions.
EventItemMatterName: Regulation of illegal alterations and conversions.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Assembly to pass A1899 and the New York State Senate to pass S1551, legislation that would require health insurance companies doing business in the State of New York to cover the cost of colorectal screening procedures for those over 50 years of age and for those under 50 years of age who are considered at high risk for the disease.
EventItemMatterName: Health insurance companies to cover the cost of colorectal screening procedures for those over 50 years of age.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to issuance of a certificate of completion for individuals working on supported scaffolds.
EventItemMatterName: Issuance of a certificate of fitness for individuals working on supported scaffolds.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of the United Nations’ International Conference on Population and Development Programme of Actions, also known as the “Cairo Programme of Actions,” which establishes consensus on a variety of development goals including gender equality, equity and the empowerment of women.
EventItemMatterName: Support of the UNs’ International Conference on Population and Development Programme of Actions, also known as the “Cairo Programme of Actions”.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on Congress to repeal the Weldon Refusal Clause, which would allow institutions to refuse to comply with existing or future laws that protect women’s access to abortion services.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to repeal the Weldon Refusal Clause

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Assembly Members Dinowitz, Greene, Millman and Towns A.1401 “An ACT to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to clearly marking certain pedestrian crosswalks in any city having a population on one million or more persons.”
EventItemMatterName: AN ACT, clearly marking certain pedestrian crosswalks in any city having a population of one million or more. (A.1401)

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Assembly Members Dinowitz, and Greene A.1442 “An ACT to dedicate the Jerome Park Reservoir tract in the Bronx as parkland.”
EventItemMatterName: AN ACT, to dedicate the Jerome Park Resevoir tract in the Bronx as Parkland. (A.1442)

EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Senator Maltese S.2310 and Assembly Members Cohen and Gianaris A.3477, “AN ACT to amend the retirement and social security law, in relation to the optional age fifty-five improved benefit retirement program for certain New York City members.”
EventItemMatterName:
AN ACT, the optional fifty-five improved benefit program for certain NYC members 
(S.2310. A.3477)

Smith, and M. Smith S.1282, and Assembly Member Robinson A.2455, “AN ACT to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the registration of property and designation of mailing address.”

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Senator Smith S.2077 and Assembly Member Cohen A.3634, “AN ACT to authorize retroactive membership in tier one of the New York City teachers’ retirement system for Rose Treiber.”
EventItemMatterName: AN ACT, to authorize retroactive membership in tier one of the NYC teachers' retirement system for Rose Treiber S.2077, A.3634)

EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Senator Maltese S.333 and Assembly Member Ortiz A.2196, “An Act to amend the General Business Law, in relation to adult commercial establishments.”

Amend the General Business Law, in relation to adult commercial establishments.

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Senator Maltese S. 2516 and Assembly Member Cymbrowitz A.5273, “An Act to amend the general municipal law, in relation to certain impairments of health presumed accidental or incurred in the performance of duty.”
EventItemMatterName: Amend the general municipal law, in relation to certain impairment of health presumed accidental or incurred in the performance of duty

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Senator Maltese S.2519, “An Act to amend the retirement and social security law, in relation to deputy sheriffs members of the New York City employees’ retirement system.”
EventItemMatterName: Amend the retirement and social security law, in relation to deputy sheriffs. (S.2519).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Senators Maltese, Fuschillo S.276, “An Act to amend the New York city charter, in relation to permitting police personnel to accept other offices and to repeal section 1129 of such charter relating thereto.”
EventItemMatterName: AN ACT, to permit police personnel to accept other offices. (S.276)

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Assembly Member Wright A.763, “An ACT authorizing the city of New York to reconvey its interest in certain real property acquired by in rem tax foreclosure in the borough of Manhattan to the person or persons who would have inherited said property from former owner Enola Walker, deceased, notwithstanding expiration of the two year period within which application may be made to the city to release its interest in property thus acquired; Block No. 1902, Lot No. 126 on the tax map for the borough of Manhattan.”
EventItemMatterName: In Rem, Enola Walker, Manhattan. (A.763).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Assembly Member Wright A.828, “An ACT authorizing the city of New York to reconvey its interest in certain real property acquired by in rem tax foreclosure in the borough of Manhattan to Debora Unger and Anthony Marcus, notwithstanding the expiration of the two year period with in which application may be made to the city to release its interest in property thus acquired; Block No. 2074, Lot No. 15 and Block No. 1949, Lot No. 5 on the tax map for the borough of Manhattan.”
EventItemMatterName: In Rem, Debora Unger and Anthony Marcus, Manhattan. (A.828).
